Columns.Description: The timestamp (UTC) of when the log was generated.
Columns.Name: TimeGenerated

Columns.Description: The operation associated with log record.
Columns.Name: OperationName

Columns.Description: Unique identifier of the Power BI tenant.
Columns.Name: CustomerTenantId

Columns.Description: Unique identifier of the workspace being operated on.
Columns.Name: WorkspaceId

Columns.Description: Unique identifier of the Premium capacity being operated on.
Columns.Name: PremiumCapacityId

Columns.Description: Property bag of unique identifiers providing details about the application executing the request. E.g. report ID.
Columns.Name: ApplicationContext

Columns.Description: Contains the name of the client application that created the connection to the server. This column is populated with the values passed by the application rather than the displayed name of the program.
Columns.Name: ApplicationName

Columns.Description: The name of the computer on which the client application is running. This column is populated with the values passed by the client application.
Columns.Name: ClientHostName

Columns.Description: Contains the process ID of the client application.
Columns.Name: ClientProcessId

Columns.Description: Unique identifier of the connection.
Columns.Name: ConnectionId

Columns.Description: Amount of CPU time (in milliseconds) used by the event.
Columns.Name: CPUTime

Columns.Description: Contains the name of the database in which the query is running.
Columns.Name: DatabaseName

Columns.Description: Amount of time (in milliseconds) taken by the event.
Columns.Name: Duration

Columns.Description: The user on whose behalf the operation is running. Used when an end user identity must be impersonated on the server.
Columns.Name: EffectiveUsername

Columns.Description: Contains the error number of any error associated with the event.
Columns.Name: Error

Columns.Description: Event Class is used to categorize events.
Columns.Name: EventClass

Columns.Description: Event Subclass provides additional information about each event class.
Columns.Name: EventSubclass

Columns.Description: Contains the integer data associated with the reported event, such as the current count of the number of rows processed for a processing event.
Columns.Name: IntegerData

Columns.Description: Contains the object ID associated with the reported event.
Columns.Name: ObjectId

Columns.Description: The name of the object for which the event occurred.
Columns.Name: ObjectName

Columns.Description: Object path. A comma-separated list of parents, starting with the object's parent.
Columns.Name: ObjectPath

Columns.Description: Object reference. Encoded as XML for all parents, using tags to describe the object.
Columns.Name: ObjectReference

Columns.Description: Identifies the type of object associated with a particular lock. For example, a lock timeout on a database will indicate the object type 100002, which is the Database object type.
Columns.Name: ObjectType

Columns.Description: An integer representing how many rows have been processed in the current operation at a point in time.
Columns.Name: ProgressTotal

Columns.Description: Contains the parameters for parameterized queries and commands associated with the event.
Columns.Name: RequestParameters

Columns.Description: Contains the properties of the XMLA request.
Columns.Name: RequestProperties

Columns.Description: Unique identifier of a session which represents multiple transactions occurring within the same scope e.g. Sharing calculated members.
Columns.Name: SessionId

Columns.Description: Contains the severity level of an exception associated with the command event. Values are: 0 = Success, 1 = Informational, 2 = Warning, 3 = Error.
Columns.Name: Severity

Columns.Description: Server process ID. This uniquely identifies a user session. This directly corresponds to the session GUID used by XML/A.
Columns.Name: SpId

Columns.Description: Contains the time at which the event started, when available.
Columns.Name: StartTime

Columns.Description: Indicates if the operation was successful. 1 = success. 0 = failure.
Columns.Name: Success

Columns.Description: Contains verbose information associated with the event
Columns.Name: TextData

Columns.Description: Unique Identifier of request
Columns.Name: RootActivityId

Columns.Description: The name of the table
Columns.Name: Type

Columns.Description: A unique identifier for the resource that the record is associated with
Columns.Name: _ResourceId

Columns.Description: A unique identifier for the subscription that the record is associated with
Columns.Name: _SubscriptionId
